    "import matplotlib\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "np.random.seed(19680801)\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from faker import Faker\n",
    "faker = Faker()\n",
    "from datetime import datetime \n",
    "from datetime import timedelta\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import math\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 199,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "d=datetime(2020, 4, 30)"
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 319,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def simulate_duration(datetime_created):\n",
    "    #p= np.random.uniform()\n",
    "    mu, sigma = 0., 1. # mean and standard deviation\n",
    "    p = np.random.lognormal(mu, sigma, 1)\n",
    "    duration= int(p*24*60)\n",
    "    end_date= datetime_created + timedelta(minutes= duration)\n",
    "    if end_date >= datetime.now():\n",
    "        return -1\n",
    "    return duration\n",
    "def simulate_assignment_team():\n",
    "    return faker.random_int(1, 5)\n",
    "def simulate_priority(n=1):\n",
    "    prio=[]\n",
    "    for p in  np.random.exponential(1,n):\n",
    "        p_cap=max(1,min(5-math.ceil(p),4))\n",
    "        prio.append (p_cap)\n",
    "    return prio"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 320,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

   "source": [

  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "source": [
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "row_list=[]\n",
    "for n in range(0,30000):\n",
    "    dict1={}\n",
    "    dict1[\"created_on\"]=faker.date_time_between(start_date='-120d', end_date='now')\n",
    "    dict1['team']= simulate_assignment_team()\n",
    "    dict1[\"duration\"]= simulate_duration(dict1[\"created_on\"])   \n",
    "    dict1[\"priority\"]= simulate_priority()[0]\n",
    "    if dict1[\"duration\"]> -1:\n",
    "        dict1[\"closed_on\"]= dict1[\"created_on\"]+ timedelta(minutes= dict1['duration'])\n",
    "        dict1['status']='Closed'\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        dict1[\"closed_on\"]=None\n",
    "        dict1['status']='Open'\n",
    "        duration_to_date=datetime.now()-dict1['created_on']\n",
    "        dict1['duration']=duration_to_date.seconds/60\n",
    "    dict1[\"duration_days\"]= dict1[\"duration\"]/(60*24)\n",
    "    row_list.append(dict1)\n",
    "df=pd.DataFrame(row_list)\n",
    "#df.set_index(\"created_on\", inplace=True)\n",
    "df.insert(0, 'id', range(8000000, 8000000 + len(df)))\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 322,
   "metadata": {},

   "source": [
    "df_day_closed = df[d==df['closed_on'].dt.floor(\"d\")]\n",
    "df['week_commencing_date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['created_on']) - pd.to_timedelta(7, unit='d')\n",
    "df['wc']= df['week_commencing_date'].dt.floor('d')\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {

   "source": [

    "#use len for count\n"

   "source": [
    "def get_queue_for_day(df, d, prio=None):\n",
    "    if prio is None:\n",
    "        df_day=df\n",
    "        priority=0\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        priority=prio\n",
    "        df_day=df[df.priority==prio]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    df_day_queue = df_day[ (df_day.created_on.dt.floor('d')<=d ) & ((df_day.closed_on.dt.floor('d') >= d ) | (df_day.closed_on.isnull()))]\n",
    "    df_day_created =df_day_queue[d==df_day_queue['created_on'].dt.floor(\"d\")]\n",
    "    df_day_closed = df_day_queue[d==df_day_queue['closed_on'].dt.floor(\"d\")]\n",
    "    return [len(df_day_queue),len(df_day_created), len(df_day_closed),priority]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 326,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def simulate_period(start_date,end_date,prio=None):\n",
    "    sim_period=[]\n",
    "    delta = timedelta(days=1)\n",
    "    d=start_date\n",
    "    while d <= end_date:\n",
    "        row= [d]+get_queue_for_day(df,d,prio)\n",
    "        sim_period.append(row)\n",
    "        d += delta\n",
    "    return sim_period"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "sim_all=simulate_period(datetime(2020,3,1),datetime.now())\n",

    "sim_p2=simulate_period(datetime(2020,3,1),datetime.now(),2)\n",
    "sim_p3=simulate_period(datetime(2020,3,1),datetime.now(),3)\n",
    "sim_p4=simulate_period(datetime(2020,3,1),datetime.now(),4)"
   ]
